               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18440916-name-725" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18440916-name-725" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18440916-name-725" type="surname" value="LITCHFIELD"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18440916-name-725" type="given" value="JOHN"></interp>JOHN LITCHFIELD</persName>
                  </hi>. I am a builder, living in Bethnal-green—I am re-building the Lunatic Asylum there—the prisoner was employed by me as a labourer—here are five boards—I believe them to be part of what I had there—the prisoner had no authority to take them.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Cross-examined by</hi> 
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">MR. WILDE</hi>. <hi rend="italic">Q.</hi> Were there many other labourers there? <hi rend="italic">A.</hi> Yes.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18440916-name-726" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18440916-name-726" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18440916-name-726" type="surname" value="JAMES"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18440916-name-726" type="given" value="JOHN"></interp>JOHN JAMES</persName>
                  </hi>. On the 12th of Sept. I was passing the Asylum, and saw the prisoner putting boards over the palings—I then saw him coming through the hedge with one or two of them—he put them together, and took them to the furthest end of the wall, and got over the fence himself—he carried them away—I followed him into Sugar-loaf-alley—he said to me, "You have been following me with these boards "—I said, "Yes, I have, you had better take them back "—he said, "I had them given to me;"—he then said he bought them, and abused me—the officer came up, and I gave him in charge.</p>
               <p>(The prisoner received a good character.)</p>
